<h2>Content Strategy for Storage Facilities</h2>
<p>Most storage facility websites have a homepage, an about page, a unit sizes page, and a contact form. That is not enough for Google to rank you against competitors or REITs with hundreds of pages.</p>
<p>The storage facilities that dominate local search publish useful, specific content consistently. Not marketing fluff. Practical information that renters actually search for.</p>
<h3>Content Categories That Work</h3>
<p><strong>Unit size guides.</strong> "What Fits in a 5x10 Storage Unit?" or "10x10 Storage Unit: Size, Cost, and What It Holds." These are among the highest-searched storage keywords. Renters want to know exactly which unit to rent before they visit.</p>
<p><strong>Moving and packing guides.</strong> "How to Pack a Storage Unit to Maximize Space" or "Moving Checklist: Using Storage During a Relocation." Moving is the primary trigger for storage rentals. Content that helps movers naturally leads to storage bookings.</p>
<p><strong>Feature comparisons.</strong> "Climate Controlled vs Regular Storage: Do You Need It?" or "Indoor vs Outdoor Storage Units: Pros and Cons." Comparison content captures renters who are undecided on features.</p>
<p><strong>Location-specific pages.</strong> "Storage Units in [City]" or "Self Storage Near [Neighborhood]." Create a unique landing page for every city and neighborhood your facility serves. Each page targets a different geographic search.</p>
<p><strong>Seasonal content.</strong> "Summer Moving Season: Storage Tips for Peak Demand" or "Holiday Storage: How to Store Decorations Safely." Seasonal content ranks for recurring annual searches.</p>
<p><strong>Business storage guides.</strong> "Small Business Storage: What You Need to Know" or "How to Use Self Storage for Inventory Management." Business renters tend to stay longer and rent larger units. They represent higher lifetime value.</p>
<h3>Publishing Frequency</h3>
<p>Publishing 4 to 8 articles per month creates enough momentum to outrank competitors who publish nothing. Research from <a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/blogging-frequency">HubSpot</a> shows businesses publishing 16+ posts per month get 3.5x more traffic than those publishing 0 to 4.</p>
<p>For storage facilities, consistency matters more than volume. Even 4 posts per month on unit sizes, packing tips, and local content creates a visible advantage within 3 to 6 months.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Storage facility content strategy showing blog topics by category" src="/images/blog/storage-facility-content-strategy.webp" /></p>
