<h2>Technical SEO for Storage Facility Websites</h2>
<p>A clean, fast website is the foundation of storage facility SEO. If Google cannot crawl your site properly, no amount of content or reviews will help.</p>
<h3>Mobile-First Design</h3>
<p>Over 60% of storage searches happen on mobile. Renters search from their phones while planning a move or driving to a new apartment. Google uses mobile-first indexing.</p>
<p>Check these items:</p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Pages load in under 2.5 seconds on mobile</li>
<li>[ ] Unit availability and pricing visible without scrolling</li>
<li>[ ] Phone number is clickable (tap-to-call)</li>
<li>[ ] Online reservation forms work on mobile</li>
<li>[ ] Address links to Google Maps for driving directions</li>
</ul>
<h3>Schema Markup</h3>
<p>Schema markup tells Google exactly what your business offers. For storage facilities, use the <code>SelfStorage</code> schema type (a subtype of <code>LocalBusiness</code>).</p>
<p>Add schema for:</p>
<ul>
<li>Business name, address, and phone number</li>
<li>Hours of operation (gate hours and office hours)</li>
<li>Unit types with sizes and pricing</li>
<li>Amenities (climate control, drive-up, 24-hour access)</li>
<li>Reviews and aggregate ratings</li>
<li>Geographic service area</li>
</ul>
<p>For implementation help, read our <a href="/blog/schema-markup-seo-guide/">schema markup SEO guide</a>. Use our free <a href="/tools/schema-markup-generator/">schema markup generator</a> to create the JSON-LD.</p>
<h3>Page Speed</h3>
<p>Slow websites lose renters. <a href="https://web.dev/articles/vitals">Google research</a> shows pages loading over 3 seconds see a 53% higher bounce rate. For a renter comparing 3 facilities, a slow-loading website means they book with the competitor whose page loaded first.</p>
<p>Quick improvements:</p>
<ul>
<li>Compress all facility photos before uploading</li>
<li>Use WebP image format instead of PNG or JPEG</li>
<li>Enable browser caching</li>
<li>Remove unused scripts and plugins</li>
<li>Minimize CSS and JavaScript files</li>
</ul>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Technical SEO checklist for storage facility websites" src="/images/blog/storage-facility-technical-seo.webp" /></p>
<p>Run our free <a href="/tools/seo-audit/">SEO audit tool</a> to find technical issues on your site.</p>
