<p><strong>Create city-specific landing pages.</strong> Write unique content for every city and neighborhood you serve. Not template pages. Genuinely unique content that mentions local landmarks, nearby businesses, and area-specific storage needs.</p>
<p><strong>Respond to reviews personally.</strong> REITs use corporate review response templates. You can respond as the owner with personal, specific replies. Google and renters both notice the difference.</p>
<p><strong>Build local backlinks.</strong> REITs do not partner with local moving companies or apartment complexes in your city. You can. Those hyperlocal backlinks carry more weight in local rankings than national brand authority.</p>
<p><strong>Publish local content.</strong> "Best Moving Tips for [Your City]" or "Storage Demand During [Your City] College Move-In Season." REITs will never write content this specific. That specificity is your ranking advantage.</p>
